Paper: hep-th/9811187

Date: 1998-11-20

Title: Large N wormhole approach to spacetime foam

Comments: Revtex 3.0, 12 pages, accepted in Phys. Lett. B, Acknowledgements

includedJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B446 (1999) 135-142

A simple model of spacetime foam, made by $N$ wormholes in a semiclassicalapproximation, is taken under examination. We show that the qualitativebehaviour of the fluctuation of the metric conjectured by Wheeler is herereproduced.